## Certificate balance

> Headers

```
Content-type: application/json
```

> Request example

```shell
curl https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/balance?shop_id=...&shop_secret=...&code=...
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "payload": {
      "status": "active",
      "code": "...",
      "balance": 5000,
      "nominal": 5000,
      "personal": false,
      "activated_date": "...",
      "expiration_date": "...",
      "deactivated_date": "...",
      "expiration_days": 30,
      "certificate_pool_code": "...",
      "streams": ["..."],
      "min_order_value": 50,
      "payable_order_share": 90
    }
}
```

Returns certificate's status, balance and main properties.

### HTTP Request


`GET https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/balance`
### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description                                                         |
|-------------|----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key                                                        |
| shop_secret | true     | Your API secret key                                                 |
| code        | true     | Certificate code                                                    |





